1
00:01:39,225 --> 00:01:42,394
This is Zero One Alpha.
We have secured Falcon.

2
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:45,606
I say again, we have secured Falcon.

3
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:48,234
By the time I count to ten...

4
00:01:48,317 --> 00:01:50,528
...you will have told me
exactly what I need to know.

5
00:01:50,986 --> 00:01:51,946
If not...

6
00:01:52,530 --> 00:01:56,033
...the number ten will be the
last thing you will ever hear.

7
00:01:56,242 --> 00:01:57,076
One

8
00:01:57,368 --> 00:01:58,035
Two

9
00:01:58,369 --> 00:01:58,702
Three

10
00:01:59,495 --> 00:02:00,204
Four

11
00:02:00,704 --> 00:02:01,622
Five

12
00:02:01,747 --> 00:02:02,665
Six

13
00:02:02,873 --> 00:02:03,791
Seven

14
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:04,542
Eight

15
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:06,377
Grenade! Sir, get back!

16
00:02:20,724 --> 00:02:22,059
Shit.

17
00:02:22,643 --> 00:02:24,270
Fucking missed it.

18
00:02:24,728 --> 00:02:26,897
How did I fucking miss it?

19
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:32,695
Merlin, I apologize for putting
you in this position.

20
00:02:32,862 --> 00:02:34,405
You trained him well.

21
00:02:35,406 --> 00:02:36,949
James...

22
00:02:37,783 --> 00:02:41,203
training is over.

23
00:02:42,454 --> 00:02:44,456
Welcome to Kingsman.

24
00:02:44,957 --> 00:02:46,250
Lancelot.

25
00:02:46,417 --> 00:02:47,418
Sir.

26
00:02:50,713 --> 00:02:54,758
I'll deal with this mess personally.

27
00:02:59,763 --> 00:03:02,933
I very much regret that your husband's
bravery can't be publicly celebrated.

28
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:04,393
I hope you understand.

29
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:06,061
How can I understand?

30
00:03:06,228 --> 00:03:08,230
You won't tell me anything.

31
00:03:09,106 --> 00:03:11,609
I didn't even know
he wasn't with his squad.

32
00:03:11,775 --> 00:03:12,943
I'm so sorry, I can't say more.

33
00:03:14,653 --> 00:03:16,447
But I would like to present you
with this Medal of Valor...

34
00:03:16,614 --> 00:03:20,951
and if you look closely on the back,
there's a number.

35
00:03:21,327 --> 00:03:23,829
And as a more concrete gesture
of our gratitude...

36
00:03:23,996 --> 00:03:25,915
we'd like to offer you...

37
00:03:27,291 --> 00:03:28,459
Let's call it a favor.

38
00:03:28,626 --> 00:03:30,127
The nature of it is your choice.

39
00:03:30,294 --> 00:03:31,629
Just tell the operator...

40
00:03:32,129 --> 00:03:35,507
"oxfords not brogues,"
and then I'll know it's you.

41
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,511
I don't want your help!

42
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:42,097
I want my husband back!

43
00:03:49,939 --> 00:03:51,106
What's your name, young man?

44
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:52,524
Eggs)'-

45
00:03:52,775 --> 00:03:54,109
Hello, Eggs)!-

46
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:56,528
Can I see that?

47
00:04:03,327 --> 00:04:05,287
You take care of this, Eggsy.

48
00:04:06,288 --> 00:04:07,665
All right?

49
00:04:11,669 --> 00:04:13,212
And take care of your mum, too.

50
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:57,715
So sorry, Professor Arnold.
Just a tiny bit more.

51
00:04:57,881 --> 00:05:00,384
For God's sakes, just rip it off.

52
00:05:00,551 --> 00:05:04,096
I'm under very strict instructions
not to hurt you.

53
00:05:04,263 --> 00:05:06,515
Look, you've made a mistake.

54
00:05:06,682 --> 00:05:09,435
I'm a university lecturer.
I've got no money.

55
00:05:09,601 --> 00:05:11,061
This isn't about money.

56
00:05:11,228 --> 00:05:13,188
Our boss just wants to talk to you.

57
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:15,274
Am I meant to find that reassuring?

58
00:05:15,441 --> 00:05:17,568
He'll be here soon. He'll explain.

59
00:05:18,736 --> 00:05:20,362
Do you like whiskey?

60
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:23,741
Red, get the '62 Dalmore.

61
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:28,120
Honestly, this whiskey, it's amazing.

62
00:05:28,454 --> 00:05:30,247
You will shit.

63
00:05:49,767 --> 00:05:52,936
I suppose asking to borrow
a cup of sugar is a step too far?

64
00:06:15,834 --> 00:06:19,797
Professor Arnold,
I'm here to take you home.

65
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:32,434
1962 Dalmore.

66
00:06:32,851 --> 00:06:34,686
It'd be a sin to spill any.

67
00:06:35,437 --> 00:06:36,814
Don't you think?

68
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:19,690
Can you hold these? Please?

69
00:07:33,954 --> 00:07:34,872
Thank you.

70
00:07:41,587 --> 00:07:43,547
Everything is clean.

71
00:07:49,261 --> 00:07:52,055
My kind of welcome.

72
00:07:59,438 --> 00:08:01,565
No stomach for violence.

73
00:08:01,732 --> 00:08:03,650
I mean, literally,
I see one drop of blood...

74
00:08:03,817 --> 00:08:05,736
that is me done.

75
00:08:05,903 --> 00:08:07,070
I'm like...

76
00:08:07,237 --> 00:08:08,572
projectile.

77
00:08:08,739 --> 00:08:10,908
Listen, I'm so sorry...

78
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:16,455
you had to witness all this unpleasantness
due to our uninvited guest.

79
00:08:16,622 --> 00:08:20,751
But I promise you, by the time
I've found out who he works for...

80
00:08:20,918 --> 00:08:25,255
you and I will be the best of friends.

81
00:08:31,845 --> 00:08:33,889
To the shop, please.

82
00:08:57,204 --> 00:08:58,372
Arthur's in the dining room, sir.

83
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:10,008
Arthur.

84
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:11,385
Galahad.

85
00:09:11,635 --> 00:09:16,265
The others were beginning to wonder
if we were going to have a double toast.

86
00:09:18,976 --> 00:09:22,938
Gentlemen, I'm thankful to
say it's been 17 years...

87
00:09:23,105 --> 00:09:25,482
since we last had occasion
to use this decanter.

88
00:09:26,358 --> 00:09:30,779
Lancelot was an outstanding agent,
and a true Kingsman.

89
00:09:30,946 --> 00:09:32,364
He will be sorely missed.

90
00:09:33,740 --> 00:09:34,908
To Lancelot.

91
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,411
To Lancelot.

92
00:09:41,456 --> 00:09:46,461
I intend to start the selection process
for Lancelot's replacement tomorrow.

93
00:09:46,753 --> 00:09:49,172
I want each of you
to propose a candidate...

94
00:09:49,339 --> 00:09:51,675
and have them report to UK HQ...

95
00:09:51,883 --> 00:09:54,011
no later than 9 p.m. GMT.

96
00:09:54,636 --> 00:09:55,470
Thank you.

97
00:09:58,015 --> 00:09:58,849
Merlin.

98
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:01,518
Come in.

99
00:10:01,977 --> 00:10:04,563
Lancelot was investigating
a group of mercenaries...

100
00:10:04,730 --> 00:10:07,441
who were experimenting
with biological weaponry.

101
00:10:07,608 --> 00:10:08,609
Glasses, gentlemen, please.

102
00:10:11,278 --> 00:10:13,614
Uganda,2012.

103
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,282
Synthetic cathinones.

104
00:10:15,449 --> 00:10:18,869
They put it in the water supply
of a guerrilla army base.

105
00:10:19,036 --> 00:10:22,289
Rage, cannibalism, multiple fatalities.

106
00:10:23,624 --> 00:10:25,125
Chechnya, 2013.

107
00:10:25,459 --> 00:10:27,085
Insurgents turned on one another.

108
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:31,006
Indisputably, the work of our mercenaries,
but no trace of any chemicals of any kind.

109
00:10:31,173 --> 00:10:32,257
So what happened to Lancelot?

110
00:10:33,258 --> 00:10:36,261
He tracked them to this property
in Argentina.

111
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:37,763
While he had them under surveillance...

112
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:39,765
he became aware
they'd effected a kidnapping.

113
00:10:40,599 --> 00:10:44,603
So he executed a solo rescue mission,
which failed.

114
00:10:45,479 --> 00:10:46,980
This is his last transmission.

115
00:10:48,982 --> 00:10:51,526
-Who is he?
-Some climate change doomsayer.

116
00:10:51,693 --> 00:10:53,195
Expounds something
called "Gaia theory"...

117
00:10:53,362 --> 00:10:55,113
about the world healing itself,
or some such.

118
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:59,159
But what's curious,
is he's not actually missing.

119
00:10:59,618 --> 00:11:01,953
This is Professor Arnold...

120
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:04,164
at Imperial College this morning.

121
00:11:05,248 --> 00:11:07,000
It's all yours.

122
00:11:07,209 --> 00:11:09,461
And don't forget
your membership proposal.

123
00:11:09,628 --> 00:11:12,714
Try picking a more suitable
candidate this time.

124
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:14,758
17 years and still...

125
00:11:14,925 --> 00:11:18,553
evolving with the times remains
an entirely foreign concept to you.

126
00:11:18,762 --> 00:11:21,807
Need I remind you, I wouldn't be here
if it weren't for that young man?

127
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:24,559
He was as much Kingsman
material as any of them.

128
00:11:24,726 --> 00:11:25,936
More so.

129
00:11:26,103 --> 00:11:29,106
But he wasn't exactly one of us, was he?

130
00:11:29,898 --> 00:11:33,485
Let's face it, Galahad,
your little experiment failed.

131
00:11:35,153 --> 00:11:37,698
With respect, Arthur, you're a snob.

132
00:11:37,864 --> 00:11:38,949
"With respect"?

133
00:11:40,158 --> 00:11:42,327
The world is changing.

134
00:11:42,494 --> 00:11:46,498
There's a reason why aristocrats
developed weak chins.

135
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:05,976
Eggsy?

136
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:10,188
Eggsy, come here.

137
00:12:13,483 --> 00:12:15,193
-Got any Rizla, babe?
-No.

138
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,404
Why don't you do your mum a favor,
go down to the shop and get some?

139
00:12:17,571 --> 00:12:18,864
-Get them yourself.
-Oi.

140
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:21,700
What have I said to you
about speaking to Dean like that?

141
00:12:21,867 --> 00:12:25,328
Three's a crowd, innit?
Why don't Dean's poodle go?

142
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:26,955
I'll tell you what.

143
00:12:27,122 --> 00:12:28,874
Why don't you take this,
go and get some Rizlas...

144
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,876
get yourself some sweets?
And while you're gone...

145
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:34,963
we'll show your mother
how three can be good company.

146
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:38,383
Thanks, babe.

147
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:47,976
There we go.

148
00:12:48,977 --> 00:12:50,145
Is that better?

149
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:07,329
If Dean treats your mum so bad,
why doesn't she leave him?

150
00:13:07,496 --> 00:13:09,456
Low self-esteem. That's her problem.

151
00:13:09,623 --> 00:13:11,374
Fuck off.
Why would she have low self-esteem?

152
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,376
Eggsy's mum is well fit.

153
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:15,879
-No offense, bruv.
-It's all right.

154
00:13:16,797 --> 00:13:19,132
One of these days,
I'm gonna smash his face in.

155
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:20,717
Are you mental, cuz?

156
00:13:20,884 --> 00:13:23,553
He'd just get that lot to do you,
and then pretend he knew nothing--

157
00:13:26,056 --> 00:13:26,932
...about it.

158
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:29,768
You think you can chat shit about us
and we won't do nothing...

159
00:13:29,935 --> 00:13:32,062
just because our guvnor's
banging Eggsy's mum?

160
00:13:32,229 --> 00:13:34,064
Pretty much, yeah.

161
00:13:34,231 --> 00:13:36,399
Bruv, just leave it. Let's just go, man.

162
00:13:36,566 --> 00:13:37,484
It's not worth it.

163
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:40,237
You boys have outstayed your welcome.

164
00:13:40,570 --> 00:13:41,404
Leave.

165
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:44,324
What?

166
00:13:45,075 --> 00:13:46,910
I'm sorry about that, bruv.

167
00:13:49,996 --> 00:13:50,789
Yeah.

168
00:13:51,081 --> 00:13:52,123
Mug.

169
00:13:54,251 --> 00:13:56,419
They weren't fucking worth it, boys.

170
00:13:57,462 --> 00:14:00,757
It's freezing. Why are we walking?

171
00:14:00,924 --> 00:14:02,759
You jacked his fucking car keys, bruv?

172
00:14:02,926 --> 00:14:05,428
Yeah. Now, we're gonna nick his car.

173
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:07,430
Shit!

174
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:14,813
Hold on, boys.

175
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:19,025
Hey, that's my fucking car!

176
00:14:19,192 --> 00:14:21,444
Hey! Hey! Eggsy!

177
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:23,655
I swear, you want to fucking stop it!

178
00:14:23,822 --> 00:14:26,366
You're a fucking dead man! Stop it!

179
00:14:29,286 --> 00:14:30,287
I'm gonna fucking have ya!

180
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:36,960
Floor it, Eggsy!

181
00:14:37,127 --> 00:14:37,961
Floor it!

182
00:14:38,837 --> 00:14:40,088
Wanker!

183
00:14:41,923 --> 00:14:43,425
Yeah, Dean. Look, it's me.

184
00:14:43,592 --> 00:14:45,594
Eggsy just stole my fucking car.

185
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:48,597
I've come out the pub,
he's done 15 donuts in my fucking face...

186
00:14:48,763 --> 00:14:50,307
and he's drove off.

187
00:14:50,473 --> 00:14:52,601
No, I can't have it!
He's disrespecting me.

188
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,978
And that means,
he's disrespecting you.

189
00:14:55,145 --> 00:14:57,981
Hold up! What the...?

190
00:15:38,855 --> 00:15:39,689
Dickhead.

191
00:15:41,733 --> 00:15:43,652
Foxes are vermin, cuz.

192
00:15:43,818 --> 00:15:45,236
Should've driven it over.

193
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:47,364
Should've done a lot of things.

194
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:49,199
I'll sort this. Get out of the car.

195
00:15:49,908 --> 00:15:51,868
I said, get out of the fucking car!

196
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:03,838
Eggsy, there is no such thing
as honor amongst thieves.

197
00:16:04,839 --> 00:16:08,551
Now, you can start giving me some names
of the boys you were with...

198
00:16:09,219 --> 00:16:10,553
or you go down.

199
00:16:11,429 --> 00:16:12,764
It's up to you.

200
00:16:13,974 --> 00:16:15,558
I want to exercise
my right to a phone call.

201
00:16:18,353 --> 00:16:21,773
Well, I hope it's to your mum...

202
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:25,443
to tell her you're gonna be
18 months late for your dinner.

203
00:16:56,391 --> 00:16:58,768
Customer Complaints, how may I help you?

204
00:16:59,561 --> 00:17:01,104
My name's Eggsy Unwin.

205
00:17:01,271 --> 00:17:05,775
Sorry, Gary Unwin.
And I'm up shit creek.

206
00:17:05,942 --> 00:17:07,193
I'm in Holborn police station...

207
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,029
and my mum said to call this number
if ever I needed help.

208
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,698
I'm sorry, sir. Wrong number.

209
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:13,199
Wait! Wait!

210
00:17:14,784 --> 00:17:17,203
Oxfords not brogues.

211
00:17:18,955 --> 00:17:20,331
Your complaint has been duly noted...

212
00:17:20,498 --> 00:17:23,626
and we hope that we have
not lost you as a loyal customer.

213
00:17:34,971 --> 00:17:36,056
Yeah.

214
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,975
You what?

215
00:17:40,310 --> 00:17:41,352


216
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:42,812
Yeah.

217
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:46,149
Yes, I totally understand.

218
00:18:05,543 --> 00:18:06,753
Eggs)'-

219
00:18:07,754 --> 00:18:08,880
Would you like a lift home?

220
00:18:09,756 --> 00:18:10,840
Who are you?

221
00:18:11,007 --> 00:18:12,342
The man who got you released.

222
00:18:12,509 --> 00:18:13,843
That ain't an answer.

223
00:18:14,177 --> 00:18:16,346
A little gratitude would be nice.

224
00:18:17,347 --> 00:18:20,850
My name is Harry Hart,
and I gave you that medal.

225
00:18:22,393 --> 00:18:24,395
Your father saved my life.

226
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:29,818
So before you was a tailor,
was you in the army?

227
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,694
Like an officer.

228
00:18:31,861 --> 00:18:33,363
Not quite.

229
00:18:33,530 --> 00:18:35,323
So where was you posted,
Iraq or something?

230
00:18:35,490 --> 00:18:37,742
Sorry, Eggsy. Classified.

231
00:18:38,827 --> 00:18:40,370
But my dad saved your life, yeah?

232
00:18:41,412 --> 00:18:44,916
The day your father died,
I missed something.

233
00:18:46,042 --> 00:18:47,168
And if it weren't for his courage...

234
00:18:47,335 --> 00:18:50,255
my mistake would have cost the lives
of every man present.

235
00:18:51,339 --> 00:18:52,674
So I owe him.

236
00:18:53,925 --> 00:18:55,885
Your father was a brave man.

237
00:18:57,095 --> 00:18:58,888
A good man.

238
00:18:59,055 --> 00:19:00,098
And having read your files...

239
00:19:00,265 --> 00:19:02,684
I think he'd be bitterly disappointed
in the choices you've made.

240
00:19:02,851 --> 00:19:04,018
You can't talk to me like that.

241
00:19:04,185 --> 00:19:05,061
Huge l.Q.

242
00:19:05,228 --> 00:19:07,105
Great performance at primary school.

243
00:19:08,022 --> 00:19:09,357
And it all went tits up.

244
00:19:09,524 --> 00:19:12,235
Drugs, petty crime. Never had a job.

245
00:19:12,402 --> 00:19:14,070
You think there's a lot of jobs
going around here, do you?

246
00:19:14,237 --> 00:19:15,738
Doesn't explain
why you gave up your hobbies.

247
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:18,491
First prize,
regional Under-10s gymnastics...

248
00:19:18,658 --> 00:19:19,868
two years in a row.

249
00:19:20,034 --> 00:19:22,245
Your coach had you pegged
as Olympic team material.

250
00:19:22,412 --> 00:19:24,080
Yeah, well, when you grow up around
someone like my stepdad...

251
00:19:24,247 --> 00:19:25,707
you pick up new hobbies pretty quick.

252
00:19:25,874 --> 00:19:27,584
Of course. Always someone else's fault.

253
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:31,004
Who's to blame
for you quitting the Marines?

254
00:19:31,171 --> 00:19:33,548
You were halfway through training,
doing brilliantly, but you gave up.

255
00:19:33,715 --> 00:19:35,717
Because my mum went mental.

256
00:19:35,884 --> 00:19:38,678
Banging on about losing me
as well as my dad.

257
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:41,264
Didn't want me being cannon fodder
for snobs like you.

258
00:19:41,431 --> 00:19:43,850
Judging people like me
from your ivory towers...

259
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:46,227
with no thought about
why we do what we do.

260
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:49,272
We ain't got much choice. You get me?

261
00:19:49,731 --> 00:19:52,108
And if we was born with the same
silver spoon up our arses...

