00:54:35,189 --> 00:54:38,192
Property, mostly.
Property and the markets.

784
00:54:38,359 --> 00:54:40,403
Nothing questionable,
if that's your concern.

785
00:54:40,569 --> 00:54:43,322
Look, I'm just into finding out
what caliber person you are.

786
00:54:43,489 --> 00:54:44,323
I'm sure you understand that.

787
00:54:44,865 --> 00:54:45,908
I most certainly do.

788
00:54:46,075 --> 00:54:47,576
-Hope you're hungry.
-I'm famished.

789
00:54:47,743 --> 00:54:48,786
Good.

790
00:54:48,869 --> 00:54:49,870
Grab a seat.

791
00:55:11,642 --> 00:55:12,727
I'll have the Big Mac, please.

792
00:55:12,893 --> 00:55:14,061
Great choice.

793
00:55:14,228 --> 00:55:17,648
But nothing beats two cheeseburgers
with secret sauce.

794
00:55:17,815 --> 00:55:19,608
Goes great with this '45 Lafite.

795
00:55:19,775 --> 00:55:20,776
A classic pairing.

796
00:55:21,193 --> 00:55:24,196
And may I suggest Twinkies
and a 1937 Chateau d'Yquem for pudding?

797
00:55:25,031 --> 00:55:26,407
I like it.

798
00:55:26,991 --> 00:55:30,786
So, you want to donate to my foundation.

799
00:55:30,953 --> 00:55:34,290
You are aware that I wound things
down in that area, right?

800
00:55:34,457 --> 00:55:37,376
Climate change is a threat,
which affects us all, Mr. Valentine.

801
00:55:37,543 --> 00:55:40,671
And you're one of the few powerful men
who seems to share my concerns.

802
00:55:40,838 --> 00:55:43,507
No, I shut things down,
because I wasn't getting anywhere.

803
00:55:43,674 --> 00:55:46,510
Every bit of research
kept pointing to the same thing.

804
00:55:46,677 --> 00:55:48,054
That carbon emissions
are a red herring...

805
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:51,891
and that we're past the point of no return
no matter what remedial actions we take?

806
00:55:52,266 --> 00:55:53,893
You know your shit.

807
00:55:54,060 --> 00:55:57,646
I sometimes envy the blissful ignorance
of those less well versed in their...

808
00:55:58,189 --> 00:55:59,398
"shit."

809
00:56:00,441 --> 00:56:01,984
As Professor Arnold always said...

810
00:56:02,568 --> 00:56:04,987
"Humankind is the only virus
cursed to live...

811
00:56:05,154 --> 00:56:08,407
"with the horrifying knowledge
of its host's fragile mortality."

812
00:56:09,658 --> 00:56:12,203
You know, not a lot of people
knew about him.

813
00:56:14,914 --> 00:56:17,291
You like spy movies, Mr. DeVere?

814
00:56:20,961 --> 00:56:24,006
Nowadays, they're all a little
serious for my taste.

815
00:56:24,173 --> 00:56:25,132
But the old ones...

816
00:56:25,925 --> 00:56:27,176
Marvelous.

817
00:56:27,343 --> 00:56:29,595
Give me a far-fetched
theatrical plot any day.

818
00:56:29,762 --> 00:56:33,265
The old Bond movies. Oh, man!

819
00:56:33,432 --> 00:56:36,977
When I was a kid, that was my dream job.

820
00:56:37,770 --> 00:56:39,355
Gentleman spy.

821
00:56:39,730 --> 00:56:43,067
I always felt the old Bond films
were only as good as the villain.

822
00:56:43,442 --> 00:56:47,571
As a child, I rather fancied a future
as a colorful megalomaniac.

823
00:56:49,448 --> 00:56:52,743
What a shame we both had to grow up.

824
00:56:57,373 --> 00:56:58,582
Bon appétit.

825
00:57:01,127 --> 00:57:04,088
Just give me a couple of days
to think over your proposal.

826
00:57:04,255 --> 00:57:05,840
I'll have my people
get in touch with yours...

827
00:57:06,006 --> 00:57:07,508
and it's all good.

828
00:57:07,675 --> 00:57:11,220
And thank you for such a happy meal.

829
00:57:16,559 --> 00:57:17,935
Well, want me to follow him?

830
00:57:18,102 --> 00:57:19,228
Nah.

831
00:57:19,520 --> 00:57:21,981
I put a nano tracker gel in the wine.

832
00:57:22,148 --> 00:57:25,151
We'll know his every move
for the next 24 hours.

833
00:57:25,317 --> 00:57:27,862
Finally find out who he works for.

834
00:57:29,447 --> 00:57:31,407
Valentine didn't let me
out of his sight.

835
00:57:31,574 --> 00:57:34,076
All I got was this on the way in.

836
00:57:38,205 --> 00:57:41,292
South Glade Mission Church
is a hate group based in Kentucky.

837
00:57:42,168 --> 00:57:43,752
FBI have been monitoring them for years.

838
00:57:43,919 --> 00:57:45,713
But you think Valentine is a supporter?

839
00:57:45,880 --> 00:57:49,175
No evidence yet of a direct connection,
but I'll keep looking.

840
00:57:50,050 --> 00:57:51,427
By the way...

841
00:57:51,594 --> 00:57:56,640
our ever-growing list of missing persons
now includes Scandinavian royalty.

842
00:57:57,057 --> 00:57:59,768
Royal Crown Princess Tilde.

843
00:58:01,854 --> 00:58:04,690
Just let me out, you psycho!

844
00:58:04,857 --> 00:58:07,693
I told you, you're free to go
any time you want.

845
00:58:07,860 --> 00:58:10,112
As long as you agree to my conditions.

846
00:58:10,529 --> 00:58:12,156
I don't agree...

847
00:58:12,323 --> 00:58:15,034
and I am never ever going to agree!

848
00:58:15,201 --> 00:58:16,452
Tough shit.

849
00:58:16,869 --> 00:58:17,870
Bitch.

850
00:58:20,039 --> 00:58:21,790
I want to speak to the British Council!

851
00:58:22,416 --> 00:58:26,837
The list of missing celebrities and dignitaries
has continued to grow in recent weeks...

852
00:58:27,004 --> 00:58:30,883
and world leaders are coming under
increasing pressure to provide answers.

853
00:58:31,050 --> 00:58:34,803
We are doing everything in our power
to find Princess Tilde.

854
00:58:34,970 --> 00:58:38,140
You know,
governments and security forces worldwide...

855
00:58:38,307 --> 00:58:42,019
are working together to find the person
behind these abductions.

856
00:58:42,186 --> 00:58:43,854
In other news,
people all over the world...

857
00:58:44,021 --> 00:58:48,400
continue to wait in line day and night
to get their free SIM cards.

858
00:58:48,567 --> 00:58:51,028
Mrs. P, did you get one?

859
00:58:51,195 --> 00:58:53,781
Yeah, I've been queuing up all day.

860
00:58:53,948 --> 00:58:58,202
This unprecedented giveaway
by the philanthropist Richmond Valentine...

861
00:58:58,369 --> 00:59:01,205
has already seen
over a billion cards distributed.

862
00:59:01,372 --> 00:59:02,581
At ease.

863
00:59:04,750 --> 00:59:07,169
So you thought we were done
for the day, huh?

864
00:59:07,962 --> 00:59:09,171
Well, we're not.

865
00:59:10,798 --> 00:59:12,800
-A party?
-Tonight, in London.

866
00:59:14,552 --> 00:59:16,887
-Who's this?
-Your target.

867
00:59:17,054 --> 00:59:19,014
Your mission
is to use your NLP training...

868
00:59:19,181 --> 00:59:21,559
to win over the individual
on the photograph in your envelope.

869
00:59:21,725 --> 00:59:23,227
And when I say "win over"...

870
00:59:23,561 --> 00:59:25,187
I do mean in the biblical sense.

871
00:59:25,354 --> 00:59:26,522
Easy.

872
00:59:27,439 --> 00:59:29,483
Posh girls love a bit of rough.

873
00:59:29,650 --> 00:59:31,277
We'll see about that, yeah?

874
00:59:31,569 --> 00:59:33,362
We certainly will.

875
00:59:38,576 --> 00:59:39,535
Hi!

876
00:59:39,702 --> 00:59:42,997
Sorry, I just had to come over
and say, amazing eyes.

877
00:59:43,372 --> 00:59:44,582
Are you wearing color contacts?

878
00:59:44,748 --> 00:59:46,959
-No!
-You so are.

879
00:59:47,126 --> 00:59:49,503
Oh, my God, negging! That's hilarious.

880
00:59:49,670 --> 00:59:51,547
I haven't heard anyone try that
since the noughties.

881
00:59:51,714 --> 00:59:52,840
Excuse me?

882
00:59:53,007 --> 00:59:53,882
"Negging-"

883
00:59:54,049 --> 00:59:58,012
Saying something negative to a pretty girl
in order to undermine her social value.

884
00:59:58,178 --> 01:00:00,222
It's supposed to make you
want to win his approval.

885
01:00:00,806 --> 01:00:03,851
Absurdly basic
neuro-linguistic programming technique.

886
01:00:04,018 --> 01:00:06,145
Is it just me, or does this champagne
taste a little bit funny?

887
01:00:06,312 --> 01:00:08,188
-It's an acquired taste, mate.
-I think it's just cheap.

888
01:00:08,355 --> 01:00:10,190
Get one of these instead.
They're delicious.

889
01:00:10,357 --> 01:00:13,068
If you're into seduction techniques,
this guy is textbook.

890
01:00:13,235 --> 01:00:15,988
See what he just did?
It's called an opinion opener.

891
01:00:16,155 --> 01:00:17,656
He got you talking
with a neutral question...

892
01:00:17,823 --> 01:00:19,533
got all of us involved
in the conversation...

893
01:00:19,700 --> 01:00:21,368
so that you craved individual attention.

894
01:00:22,077 --> 01:00:23,412
No, I'm just saying
the champagne tastes rank.

895
01:00:23,579 --> 01:00:25,331
Lady Sophie Montague-Herring.

896
01:00:25,497 --> 01:00:26,790
Phone call for you at reception.

897
01:00:26,957 --> 01:00:28,667
-Be right back.
-We'll see you in a bit, yeah?

898
01:00:28,834 --> 01:00:30,210
See you in a bit.

899
01:00:30,377 --> 01:00:32,212
Budge up, Rox. I'm feeling a bit rough.

900
01:00:32,379 --> 01:00:33,881
-Are you all right?
-No.

901
01:00:34,048 --> 01:00:35,090
Sorry to eavesdrop...

902
01:00:35,257 --> 01:00:38,802
but there's a much easier way
to guarantee getting someone home.

903
01:00:39,011 --> 01:00:40,554
Rohypnol.

904
01:00:42,723 --> 01:00:44,475
Or even something stronger.

905
01:01:02,034 --> 01:01:03,702
Who the fuck are you?

906
01:01:04,286 --> 01:01:05,704
Where am I?

907
01:01:08,123 --> 01:01:09,291
This knife...

908
01:01:09,458 --> 01:01:11,502
can save your life.

909
01:01:15,756 --> 01:01:16,757
Fuck!

910
01:01:17,174 --> 01:01:19,968
My employer's got two questions
for you, Eggsy.

911
01:01:20,135 --> 01:01:22,012
What the fuck is Kingsman?

912
01:01:22,179 --> 01:01:23,806
And who's Harry Hart?

913
01:01:23,972 --> 01:01:25,808
I don't know who the fuck that is!

914
01:01:25,974 --> 01:01:26,767
Shit!

915
01:01:26,934 --> 01:01:30,729
Eggsy, I just killed two of your friends
who gave me the same bullshit answer!

916
01:01:31,355 --> 01:01:32,272
Fuck!

917
01:01:32,731 --> 01:01:35,275
Just cut the fucking ropes, please!

918
01:01:35,442 --> 01:01:36,485
Hey, Eggsy!

919
01:01:36,652 --> 01:01:37,986
Is Kingsman worth dying for?

920
01:01:40,197 --> 01:01:41,573
FUCK you!

921
01:01:55,879 --> 01:01:57,172
Congratulations.

922
01:01:57,339 --> 01:01:58,549
Bloody well done.

923
01:02:00,843 --> 01:02:02,428
How did the others do?

924
01:02:02,594 --> 01:02:04,388
Roxy passed with flying colors.

925
01:02:04,930 --> 01:02:07,182
Charlie's up next. Want to watch?

926
01:02:08,600 --> 01:02:10,060
Yeah, all right.

927
01:02:12,563 --> 01:02:14,606
Is Kingsman really worth dying for?

928
01:02:14,773 --> 01:02:16,108
No, it fucking isn't!

929
01:02:16,275 --> 01:02:18,110
Shit, I'll tell you what you want.
Please!

930
01:02:18,277 --> 01:02:19,570
Chester King is Arthur.

931
01:02:19,737 --> 01:02:21,947
Arthur's head of a spy agency.
It's called Kingsman.

932
01:02:22,114 --> 01:02:23,657
-Get me out of here!
-Thank you, Charlie.

933
01:02:23,824 --> 01:02:25,159
Much appreciated.

934
01:02:25,325 --> 01:02:27,703
Come on!
That wasn't the fucking deal!

935
01:02:28,120 --> 01:02:30,414
Fuck!

936
01:02:37,421 --> 01:02:39,715
I had such high hopes for you.

937
01:02:39,923 --> 01:02:41,842
You're a bloody disgrace.

938
01:02:42,009 --> 01:02:43,010
Arthur, I'm sorry.

939
01:02:43,844 --> 01:02:45,179
At least untie me.

940
01:02:45,512 --> 01:02:46,847
Untie yourself.

941
01:02:48,515 --> 01:02:50,684
Arthur, please.

942
01:02:52,019 --> 01:02:54,563
I'm the fucking son of the... Shit!

943
01:02:54,730 --> 01:02:57,232
Anyone? Hello?

944
01:02:57,399 --> 01:02:59,943
Galahad, Percival, congratulations.

945
01:03:00,235 --> 01:03:03,030
Your candidates have reached
the final stage of the testing process.

946
01:03:03,197 --> 01:03:06,742
As tradition allows,
you now have 24 hours to spend with them.

947
01:03:07,367 --> 01:03:10,537
Eggsy, you should know your
father reached this point.

948
01:03:11,288 --> 01:03:12,289
From now on...

949
01:03:12,748 --> 01:03:14,208
there are no safety nets, understood?

950
01:03:18,086 --> 01:03:18,962
Good. Dismissed.

951
01:03:22,925 --> 01:03:25,052
Charlie, time to go home.

952
01:03:25,219 --> 01:03:26,553
Fuck you.

953
01:03:26,970 --> 01:03:29,223
Fucking dad's gonna hear about this!

954
01:03:31,391 --> 01:03:32,392
"To pee or not to pee?"

955
01:03:34,645 --> 01:03:35,646
That was the headline...

956
01:03:35,729 --> 01:03:38,398
the day after I defused
a dirty bomb in Paris.

957
01:03:38,899 --> 01:03:40,567
"Germany, 1, England, 5."

958
01:03:40,734 --> 01:03:41,819
Missed that game.

959
01:03:41,985 --> 01:03:44,947
I was breaking up an undercover
spy ring at the Pentagon.

960
01:03:50,452 --> 01:03:51,745
My first mission.

961
01:03:51,912 --> 01:03:53,413
Foiled the assassination
of Margaret Thatcher.

962
01:03:54,915 --> 01:03:56,250
Not everybody would
thank you for that one.

963
01:03:56,667 --> 01:03:59,419
The point is, Eggsy,
nobody thanked me for any of them.

964
01:04:00,087 --> 01:04:03,632
Front page news on all these occasions
was celebrity nonsense.

965
01:04:03,924 --> 01:04:07,469
Because it's the nature of Kingsman
that our achievements remain secret.

966
01:04:07,928 --> 01:04:11,265
A gentleman's name should appear
in the newspaper only three times.

967
01:04:11,431 --> 01:04:13,767
When he's born, when he marries,
and when he dies.

968
01:04:13,934 --> 01:04:17,104
And we are, first and foremost,
gentlemen.

969
01:04:17,437 --> 01:04:18,772
That's me fucked then.

970
01:04:19,773 --> 01:04:21,650
It's like Charlie said. I'm just a pleb.

971
01:04:21,817 --> 01:04:22,818
Nonsense.

972
01:04:22,985 --> 01:04:25,487
Being a gentleman has nothing to do
with the circumstances of one's birth.

973
01:04:26,446 --> 01:04:28,282
Being a gentleman
is something one learns.

974
01:04:29,032 --> 01:04:30,868
Yeah, but how?

975
01:04:31,785 --> 01:04:33,036
All right, first lesson.

976
01:04:33,203 --> 01:04:34,621
You should've asked me
before you took a seat.

977
01:04:36,498 --> 01:04:37,624
Second lesson...

978
01:04:38,625 --> 01:04:39,960
how to make a proper martini.

979
01:04:40,961 --> 01:04:43,046
Yes, Harry.

980
01:04:45,632 --> 01:04:48,677
Goddamn it! This fucking hurts!

981
01:04:49,177 --> 01:04:51,680
You're the one who asked
for a biometric security system.

982
01:04:51,847 --> 01:04:52,973
What's wrong with a simple switch?

983
01:04:53,140 --> 01:04:54,141
A simple switch?

984
01:04:54,308 --> 01:04:57,978
This is an extremely dangerous machine.

985
01:04:58,145 --> 01:05:02,691
It should only be operated by someone
as responsible and sane as me.

986
01:05:02,900 --> 01:05:05,152
Bad shit could happen
if this falls into the wrong hands.

987
01:05:08,363 --> 01:05:10,032
We done here? Shit!

988
01:05:10,198 --> 01:05:12,826
No. Now this one.

989
01:05:12,993 --> 01:05:14,036
For the test at the church.

990
01:05:14,202 --> 01:05:16,038
This one just has a short range.

991
01:05:16,204 --> 01:05:17,748
A simple switch will do.

992
01:05:23,712 --> 01:05:26,590
So are you gonna teach me how to
talk proper, like in My Fair Lady?

993
01:05:26,757 --> 01:05:28,216
Don't be absurd.

994
01:05:28,508 --> 01:05:31,053
Being a gentleman has nothing
to do with one's accent.

995
01:05:31,219 --> 01:05:33,513
It's about being at ease
in one's own skin.

996
01:05:33,680 --> 01:05:35,223
As Hemingway said,
"There is nothing noble...

997
01:05:35,390 --> 01:05:37,768
"in being superior to your fellow man.

998
01:05:38,185 --> 01:05:41,688
"True nobility is being superior
to your former self."

999
01:05:45,400 --> 01:05:48,737
Now, the first thing every
gentleman needs is a good suit.

1000
01:05:48,904 --> 01:05:52,199
By which I mean, a bespoke suit.
Never off-the-peg.

1001
01:05:52,366 --> 01:05:54,743
And Kingsman suits
are always bulletproof.

1002
01:05:54,910 --> 01:05:57,704
So let's get you measured,
and then, whether you get the job or not...

1003
01:05:57,871 --> 01:06:02,250
you'll have a lasting and useful memento
of your time at Kingsman.

1004
01:06:02,417 --> 01:06:06,046
I'm so sorry, sir, but a gentleman
is completing his fitting.

1005
01:06:06,213 --> 01:06:08,382
Fitting Room Two is available.

1006
01:06:08,548 --> 01:06:12,552
One does not use Fitting Room Two
when one is popping one's cherry.

1007
01:06:13,637 --> 01:06:16,431
Perhaps I'll show you Fitting Room Three
while we wait.

1008
01:06:26,817 --> 01:06:28,068
So we going up or down?

1009
01:06:28,235 --> 01:06:29,403
Neither.

1010
01:06:30,654 --> 01:06:31,655
Is this it?

1011
01:06:31,822 --> 01:06:34,908
Of course not.
Pull the hook on your left.

1012
01:06:42,165 --> 01:06:42,916
Oh, yes.

1013
01:06:43,417 --> 01:06:45,585
Very, very nice.

1014
01:06:48,630 --> 01:06:51,133
You're going to need a pair of shoes
to go with your suit.

1015
01:06:51,299 --> 01:06:55,429
An oxford is any formal shoe
with open lacing.

1016
01:06:55,595 --> 01:06:58,807
This additional decorative piece
is called broguing.

1017
01:06:58,974 --> 01:07:00,142
"Oxfords not brogues."

1018
01:07:00,308 --> 01:07:01,935
Words to live by, Eggsy.

1019
01:07:02,144 --> 01:07:04,771
Words to live by. Try a pair.

1020
01:07:05,522 --> 01:07:07,274
Your weapon scores are excellent,
by the way.

1021
01:07:08,442 --> 01:07:11,695
These you are familiar with,
and this is our standard issue pistol.

1022
01:07:11,862 --> 01:07:13,488
It's quite unique, as you'll see.

1023
01:07:13,655 --> 01:07:16,992
It also fires a shotgun cartridge
for use in messy close-range situations.

1024
01:07:17,159 --> 01:07:18,618
-How do they feel?
-Yeah, good.

1025
01:07:18,785 --> 01:07:20,120
Now do your very best impersonation...

1026
01:07:20,287 --> 01:07:21,955
of a German aristocrat's
formal greeting.

1027
01:07:25,500 --> 01:07:26,710
No, Eggsy.

1028
01:07:30,839 --> 01:07:32,090
That is sick.

1029
01:07:33,133 --> 01:07:35,093
In the old days,
they had a phone in the heel as well.

1030
01:07:35,260 --> 01:07:36,303
How do I get it back in?

1031
01:07:36,470 --> 01:07:40,348
Well, it's coated in one of the fastest
