01:26:56,378 --> 01:26:59,632
And we only drink it
when we lose a Kingsman.

1286
01:27:00,299 --> 01:27:03,302
Galahad was very fond of you.

1287
01:27:05,471 --> 01:27:07,890
And on this occasion...

1288
01:27:08,057 --> 01:27:11,393
I think it's acceptable for us
to bend the rules a little.

1289
01:27:13,812 --> 01:27:14,980
Are these all Kingsmen?

1290
01:27:15,147 --> 01:27:17,483
Yes, they're founder members.

1291
01:27:18,859 --> 01:27:20,903
I want you to join me in a toast.

1292
01:27:23,155 --> 01:27:25,157
To Galahad.

1293
01:27:26,158 --> 01:27:27,660
To Galahad.

1294
01:27:32,206 --> 01:27:34,833
Harry says you don't like
to break rules, Arthur.

1295
01:27:35,334 --> 01:27:36,418
Why now?

1296
01:27:36,585 --> 01:27:37,836
You're very good, Eggsy.

1297
01:27:38,003 --> 01:27:41,590
Perhaps I will make you my proposal
for Galahad's position.

1298
01:27:42,508 --> 01:27:45,219
Provided, of course,
that we can see eye to eye...

1299
01:27:45,386 --> 01:27:47,513
on certain political matters.

1300
01:27:50,349 --> 01:27:51,892
Can you guess...

1301
01:27:53,018 --> 01:27:54,603
what this is?

1302
01:27:54,770 --> 01:27:56,438
I don't have to. Harry showed me.

1303
01:27:56,605 --> 01:27:58,107
You click it. I die.

1304
01:27:58,274 --> 01:28:00,067
I thought that brandy tasted a bit shit.

1305
01:28:02,027 --> 01:28:02,695
Bravo.

1306
01:28:03,362 --> 01:28:06,532
Valentine won you over, somehow.

1307
01:28:06,699 --> 01:28:09,535
Once he explained, I understood.

1308
01:28:09,702 --> 01:28:10,953
When you get a virus...

1309
01:28:11,245 --> 01:28:12,454
you get a fever.

1310
01:28:12,621 --> 01:28:16,625
That's the human body raising
its core temperature to kill the virus.

1311
01:28:16,792 --> 01:28:19,044
Planet Earth works the same way.

1312
01:28:19,211 --> 01:28:21,130
Global warming is the fever.

1313
01:28:21,297 --> 01:28:24,091
Mankind is the virus.

1314
01:28:24,258 --> 01:28:26,635
We're making our planet sick.

1315
01:28:26,802 --> 01:28:29,388
A cull is our only hope.

1316
01:28:29,555 --> 01:28:31,807
If we don't reduce
our population ourselves...

1317
01:28:31,974 --> 01:28:34,560
there is only one of two ways
this can go.

1318
01:28:34,727 --> 01:28:38,981
The host kills the virus,
or the virus kills the host.

1319
01:28:39,273 --> 01:28:40,149
Either way...

1320
01:28:40,316 --> 01:28:42,776
The result is the same.

1321
01:28:42,943 --> 01:28:44,570
The virus dies.

1322
01:28:45,654 --> 01:28:49,074
So Valentine's gonna take care
of the population problem himself.

1323
01:28:49,241 --> 01:28:51,744
Well, if we don't do something,
nature will.

1324
01:28:51,910 --> 01:28:56,248
Sometimes a culling is the only way
to ensure that this species survives...

1325
01:28:56,957 --> 01:28:59,084
and history will see Valentine...

1326
01:28:59,251 --> 01:29:01,503
as the man who saved
humanity from extinction.

1327
01:29:02,087 --> 01:29:05,424
And he gets to pick and choose
who gets culled, does he?

1328
01:29:05,591 --> 01:29:06,800
All his rich mates, they get to live...

1329
01:29:06,967 --> 01:29:09,470
and anyone he thinks is worth saving,
he's keeping them safe...

1330
01:29:09,636 --> 01:29:11,597
whether they agree with him or not.

1331
01:29:11,764 --> 01:29:13,932
And you, Eggsy.

1332
01:29:14,475 --> 01:29:16,435
In Harry's honor...

1333
01:29:16,602 --> 01:29:21,273
I am inviting you
to be part of a new world.

1334
01:29:23,359 --> 01:29:25,652
It's time to make your decision.

1335
01:29:32,534 --> 01:29:34,495
I'd rather be with Harry.

1336
01:29:35,120 --> 01:29:36,038
Thanks.

1337
01:29:36,789 --> 01:29:38,165
So be it.

1338
01:29:54,473 --> 01:29:57,726
The problem with us common types...

1339
01:29:57,893 --> 01:29:59,478
is that we're light-fingered.

1340
01:30:00,687 --> 01:30:02,398
Kingsman's taught me a lot...

1341
01:30:02,564 --> 01:30:03,816
but sleight of hand...

1342
01:30:04,483 --> 01:30:06,235
Yes, they're founder members.

1343
01:30:08,862 --> 01:30:10,155
I had that down already.

1344
01:30:12,491 --> 01:30:16,078
You dirty little fucking...

1345
01:30:16,245 --> 01:30:17,663
prick.

1346
01:30:51,947 --> 01:30:53,699
It's okay, Lancelot. Put it down.

1347
01:30:54,867 --> 01:30:56,410
It's verified.

1348
01:30:58,787 --> 01:31:01,373
Arthur's phone is receiving update
texts about getting to safety.

1349
01:31:01,540 --> 01:31:03,292
-We don't have a lot of time.
-What are you going to do?

1350
01:31:03,459 --> 01:31:05,586
The question is,
what are we going to do?

1351
01:31:05,752 --> 01:31:08,464
God knows who's in Valentine's pocket
and who's not.

1352
01:31:09,131 --> 01:31:10,632
We have no choice.

1353
01:31:11,717 --> 01:31:13,802
We are gonna have to deal
with this ourselves.

1354
01:31:17,222 --> 01:31:18,557
Follow me.

1355
01:31:37,451 --> 01:31:38,744
What the fuck is this?

1356
01:31:38,911 --> 01:31:40,746
I have no idea.

1357
01:31:41,747 --> 01:31:42,915
What you're playing with...

1358
01:31:43,081 --> 01:31:45,792
is a prototype personal
transatmospheric vehicle.

1359
01:31:45,959 --> 01:31:48,253
It was developed as part of
Reagan's Star Wars project.

1360
01:31:48,420 --> 01:31:51,340
It's pretty basic,
but it should still work.

1361
01:31:51,590 --> 01:31:53,967
We're gonna take out
one of Valentine's satellites.

1362
01:31:54,343 --> 01:31:56,803
We're gonna break the chain,
stop the signal.

1363
01:31:56,970 --> 01:31:58,639
It'll take him a couple of hours
to reroute it...

1364
01:31:59,306 --> 01:32:03,685
which buys us enough time for you
to get me into Valentine's mainframe...

1365
01:32:03,852 --> 01:32:05,646
so I can shut it down.

1366
01:32:05,812 --> 01:32:08,106
Lancelot, you're going to be using it.

1367
01:32:08,273 --> 01:32:09,650
Get into your halo suit.

1368
01:32:22,287 --> 01:32:24,039
Swedish Prime Minister,
requesting permission to land.

1369
01:32:30,045 --> 01:32:31,797
Permission granted.

1370
01:32:35,384 --> 01:32:37,886
-Please.
-Thank you.

1371
01:32:38,053 --> 01:32:40,138
-How many more are we expecting?
-Not many.

1372
01:32:40,305 --> 01:32:41,640
Most have their own bunkers.

1373
01:32:41,807 --> 01:32:45,143
I figure we're just getting
the really nervous ones.

1374
01:32:45,394 --> 01:32:47,396
Welcome, Prime Minister.

1375
01:32:48,689 --> 01:32:51,650
It seems the implant
can emit some kind of counter signal...

1376
01:32:51,817 --> 01:32:55,487
to ensure the wearer remains unaffected
by the waves from the SIM cards.

1377
01:32:55,654 --> 01:32:57,698
The waves that turn everyone
into a psycho killer.

1378
01:32:57,864 --> 01:33:00,409
Quite. But what he
probably didn't tell anyone...

1379
01:33:00,576 --> 01:33:04,830
is it can also super heat
their soft tissue at his command.

1380
01:33:04,997 --> 01:33:09,167
Valentine selected his chosen few
to get the countdown warning...

1381
01:33:09,334 --> 01:33:12,170
but he had to be sure they didn't blab
to the wrong people beforehand.

1382
01:33:12,337 --> 01:33:14,047
How does this help us right now?

1383
01:33:15,007 --> 01:33:16,008
It doesn't.

1384
01:33:16,383 --> 01:33:17,759
Roxy, here we go!

1385
01:33:30,689 --> 01:33:34,276
The higher you go,
the more the balloons expand.

1386
01:33:34,443 --> 01:33:36,278
When you reach
the edge of the atmosphere...

1387
01:33:36,445 --> 01:33:38,572
they'll explode.

1388
01:33:38,739 --> 01:33:40,741
You'll need to deploy your missile
just before that, okay?

1389
01:33:40,907 --> 01:33:42,242
Edge of the atmosphere.

1390
01:33:42,409 --> 01:33:45,704
And once you've deployed,
you'll need to release for descent, fast.

1391
01:33:46,705 --> 01:33:47,956
Good luck.

1392
01:33:50,292 --> 01:33:52,294
-You can do this, okay?
-Yeah.

1393
01:33:52,461 --> 01:33:55,255
Eggsy, come on. Time is not our friend.

1394
01:34:17,736 --> 01:34:19,738
You're getting in
on Arthur's invitation.

1395
01:34:19,905 --> 01:34:21,114
You're gonna need to blend in.

1396
01:34:21,281 --> 01:34:22,407
I'm supposed to be Arthur?

1397
01:34:22,574 --> 01:34:25,577
His invitation is in his phone.
You give them this.

1398
01:34:25,744 --> 01:34:28,246
-Give his real name, Chester King.
-What about you?

1399
01:34:28,413 --> 01:34:29,831
I'm your pilot. I'm gonna stay here.

1400
01:34:30,916 --> 01:34:32,000
Is that gonna fit me?

1401
01:34:32,167 --> 01:34:34,670
A bespoke suit always fits.

1402
01:34:34,836 --> 01:34:36,630
Just be grateful
Harry had it made for you.

1403
01:34:37,589 --> 01:34:38,590
Get dressed.

1404
01:34:40,050 --> 01:34:41,093
What the fuck's wrong with them?

1405
01:34:41,426 --> 01:34:44,179
I don't know. Could have something to do
with the mass genocide.

1406
01:34:44,346 --> 01:34:46,264
Give me the mic.

1407
01:34:48,100 --> 01:34:49,643
Hey-oh!

1408
01:34:49,810 --> 01:34:52,729
Everybody, listen up! Hello, hello!

1409
01:34:52,896 --> 01:34:55,107
What the fuck is wrong with you people?

1410
01:34:55,273 --> 01:34:58,110
I just wanna remind you that today...

1411
01:34:58,276 --> 01:35:00,862
is a day of celebration.

1412
01:35:01,697 --> 01:35:05,200
We must put aside
all thoughts of death...

1413
01:35:05,367 --> 01:35:07,244
and focus on birth.

1414
01:35:08,328 --> 01:35:10,747
The birth of a new age.

1415
01:35:11,957 --> 01:35:16,920
We mustn't mourn those
who give their lives today.

1416
01:35:17,087 --> 01:35:19,047
We should honor their sacrifice...

1417
01:35:19,214 --> 01:35:21,216
Has she got my number to call me back?
I got a new phone.

1418
01:35:21,383 --> 01:35:24,553
...and their roles in saving
the human race.

1419
01:35:26,972 --> 01:35:30,642
We must put aside doubt and guilt.

1420
01:35:32,060 --> 01:35:35,605
You are the chosen people.

1421
01:35:37,232 --> 01:35:40,694
When folks tell their kids
the story of Noah's Ark...

1422
01:35:40,861 --> 01:35:41,820
is Noah the bad guy?

1423
01:35:41,987 --> 01:35:42,654
No!

1424
01:35:42,821 --> 01:35:44,823
Is God the bad guy?

1425
01:35:44,990 --> 01:35:45,657
No!

1426
01:35:45,824 --> 01:35:48,243
How about the animals
marching two by two?

1427
01:35:48,410 --> 01:35:49,202
No!

1428
01:35:49,369 --> 01:35:50,162
Of course not!

1429
01:35:51,288 --> 01:35:52,622
Yeah, that's it!

1430
01:35:52,789 --> 01:35:56,585
Let's turn those frowns upside down.

1431
01:35:56,752 --> 01:35:58,587
Eat, drink...

1432
01:35:58,754 --> 01:36:00,422
and Pam'!

1433
01:36:03,467 --> 01:36:06,011
And I will see you all in the new age.

1434
01:36:31,244 --> 01:36:33,371
Rox, it's me.

1435
01:36:33,872 --> 01:36:35,207
How's the view?

1436
01:36:38,043 --> 01:36:40,128
-Hideous
-Mine's pretty sweet.

1437
01:36:40,295 --> 01:36:43,215
-They made you one of these suits yet?
-No, not yet.

1438
01:36:43,381 --> 01:36:45,717
You've got something to
look forward to then.

1439
01:36:45,884 --> 01:36:48,470
We're coming up on Valentine's base.
Gotta go.

1440
01:36:49,930 --> 01:36:51,223
Good luck.

1441
01:36:58,897 --> 01:36:59,898
Looking good, Eggsy.

1442
01:37:02,567 --> 01:37:05,278
Feeling good, Merlin.

1443
01:37:10,575 --> 01:37:12,160
This is November-2-4-7-Charlie-Kilo...

1444
01:37:12,327 --> 01:37:14,746
requesting permission to land.

1445
01:37:17,749 --> 01:37:20,293
Permission is granted.

1446
01:37:23,964 --> 01:37:25,757
Fuck me.

1447
01:37:52,951 --> 01:37:55,412
Eggsy, we're on.

1448
01:38:10,135 --> 01:38:11,136
Chester King.

1449
01:38:12,137 --> 01:38:14,097
Mr. King, welcome.

1450
01:38:14,472 --> 01:38:18,268
I'm sure you've adhered to Valentine's
strict no-weapons policy...

1451
01:38:18,435 --> 01:38:19,769
-but if you don't object...
-Of course.

1452
01:38:19,936 --> 01:38:21,146
Thank you.

1453
01:38:21,646 --> 01:38:23,773
Do you have any luggage?

1454
01:38:24,774 --> 01:38:28,194
Congratulations, Mycroft,
you just graduated from my pilot to my valet.

1455
01:38:28,820 --> 01:38:31,281
-You cheeky-—
-Understood?

1456
01:38:31,448 --> 01:38:32,699
Good.

1457
01:38:33,992 --> 01:38:35,619
Thank you.

1458
01:39:00,894 --> 01:39:05,523
Eggsy, find a laptop, get me online.
The clock is ticking.

1459
01:39:06,691 --> 01:39:09,402
And remember, try to blend in.

1460
01:39:09,569 --> 01:39:11,529
Would sir care for a drink?

1461
01:39:12,155 --> 01:39:13,365
Martini.

1462
01:39:13,531 --> 01:39:15,700
Gin, not vodka, obviously.

1463
01:39:15,867 --> 01:39:19,579
Stirred for 10 seconds while glancing
at an unopened bottle of Vermouth.

1464
01:39:20,205 --> 01:39:21,414
Thank you.

1465
01:39:24,209 --> 01:39:26,002
Merlin, are you clocking this?

1466
01:39:26,211 --> 01:39:28,254
Yes, I am. Stay focused.

1467
01:39:28,880 --> 01:39:31,049
Lancelot, you're doing great.
Not much further to go.

1468
01:39:31,758 --> 01:39:32,884
Yes, Merlin.

1469
01:39:34,386 --> 01:39:36,680
Eggsy, get me online now.

1470
01:39:37,597 --> 01:39:38,598
Yep, I'm on it.

1471
01:39:39,766 --> 01:39:41,893
Lancelot, you're approaching
your altitude limit.

1472
01:39:42,227 --> 01:39:44,020
Those balloons won't last much longer.

1473
01:39:44,896 --> 01:39:46,856
Prepare to engage missile.

1474
01:40:02,247 --> 01:40:03,456
Society's dead.

1475
01:40:03,915 --> 01:40:05,750
Long live society.

1476
01:40:06,751 --> 01:40:08,086
Amen to that.

1477
01:40:09,546 --> 01:40:11,589
-I'm Morten Lindström.
-Chester King.

1478
01:40:11,923 --> 01:40:13,258
How'd you get online? I couldn't.

1479
01:40:13,633 --> 01:40:16,594
It's a closed network, you see.
Pre-authorized connections only.

1480
01:40:20,807 --> 01:40:22,100
I've got a fix on the satellite.

1481
01:40:22,267 --> 01:40:23,393
Do you have the correct time?

1482
01:40:23,560 --> 01:40:24,769
I think I'm still in my last time zone.

1483
01:40:24,936 --> 01:40:26,312
Yeah, yeah. Let's see now.

1484
01:40:40,410 --> 01:40:41,411
Eggsy, I'm in.

1485
01:40:41,578 --> 01:40:42,662
Get your arse back to the plane, now.

1486
01:40:42,829 --> 01:40:44,414
-On my way.
-Lancelot, good luck!

1487
01:40:44,581 --> 01:40:46,750
Firing in 3...2...

1488
01:40:54,132 --> 01:40:55,133
Nice and slow.

1489
01:40:55,300 --> 01:40:56,468
Fuck are you doing here?

1490
01:40:56,634 --> 01:40:58,970
Well, my family were invited, obviously.

1491
01:40:59,137 --> 01:41:00,764
Now, get the fuck up! Slowly.

1492
01:41:01,973 --> 01:41:03,850
Shit. Lancelot, hurry up and fire!

1493
01:41:04,017 --> 01:41:05,602
That other balloon is gonna blow!

1494
01:41:05,769 --> 01:41:08,813
Yes, Merlin. I've nearly got it.
Give me a second!

1495
01:41:10,690 --> 01:41:13,610
Valentine! I've caught a fucking spy!

1496
01:41:14,277 --> 01:41:15,320
V-Glass, zoom.

1497
01:41:15,487 --> 01:41:17,530
Oh, fuck! It's that young valet.

1498
01:41:21,659 --> 01:41:23,036
Son of a bitch.

1499
01:41:23,620 --> 01:41:24,704
Got it!

1500
01:41:34,839 --> 01:41:36,132
Oh, shit. Sound the alarm!

1501
01:41:38,676 --> 01:41:39,719
I'm not taking any chances.

1502
01:41:39,886 --> 01:41:41,387
Okay, you send out
the two-minute warning.

1503
01:41:41,554 --> 01:41:44,015
I'm starting the override.
All right, let's do this.

1504
01:41:45,350 --> 01:41:46,976
Countdown initiated.

1505
01:41:56,694 --> 01:41:58,363
-You see him?
-Right here.

1506
01:42:07,163 --> 01:42:08,414
Eggsy, take a left.

1507
01:42:09,207 --> 01:42:10,208
Two guards, up ahead.

1508
01:42:22,554 --> 01:42:23,847
Lancelot! Release now!

1509
01:42:34,899 --> 01:42:36,693
Eggsy, straight ahead, then right.

1510
01:42:37,068 --> 01:42:38,069
There's two more.

1511
01:42:41,781 --> 01:42:43,867
All right, everybody on your feet!

1512
01:42:44,033 --> 01:42:45,243
Countdown to V-day!

1513
01:42:45,410 --> 01:42:46,911
Welcome in the new age!

1514
01:42:55,295 --> 01:42:56,379
Flat spin.

1515
01:43:11,561 --> 01:43:14,397
Eggsy, next left,
down the narrow tunnel!

1516
01:43:23,156 --> 01:43:24,157
Here we go!

1517
01:43:24,324 --> 01:43:24,949
10...

1518
01:43:25,950 --> 01:43:27,285
9...

1519
01:43:27,785 --> 01:43:28,494
8...

1520
01:43:29,454 --> 01:43:30,121
7...

1521
01:43:31,372 --> 01:43:32,207
6...

1522
01:43:33,041 --> 01:43:34,125
5...

1523
01:43:34,709 --> 01:43:35,460
4...

1524
01:43:36,961 --> 01:43:37,712
3...

1525
01:43:37,879 --> 01:43:38,630
2...

1526
01:43:39,631 --> 01:43:40,506
1 !

1527
01:43:46,554 --> 01:43:48,389
Nice! Well done, both of you.

1528
01:43:49,140 --> 01:43:50,141
It's not working!

1529
01:43:50,308 --> 01:43:52,352
It's supposed to be working!
What the fuck?

1530
01:43:59,150 --> 01:43:59,817
Yes!

1531
01:43:59,984 --> 01:44:01,319
Well done, Rox. Good girl.

1532
01:44:04,697 --> 01:44:07,200
We've lost one of our satellites.

1533
01:44:16,751 --> 01:44:20,505
Oh, no, no.
There's no way I can hack past that.

1534
01:44:26,094 --> 01:44:27,095
What's going on?

1535
01:44:28,263 --> 01:44:29,347
Is there a problem?

1536
01:44:30,515 --> 01:44:31,849
Come on. There's no need for guns.

1537
01:44:32,016 --> 01:44:33,518
I'm just a pilot.

1538
01:44:36,521 --> 01:44:37,563
Fuck. Merlin!

1539
01:44:40,358 --> 01:44:41,943
Get in here!

1540
01:44:46,197 --> 01:44:47,365
Come on!

1541
01:44:50,910 --> 01:44:52,245
